This paper is about using latent variable models for conditional text generation in the context of neural machine translation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also discusses the challenges of using latent variable models for text, which suggests that it could belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions a co-attention mechanism, which is a common technique in computer vision, indicating that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the model, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which deals with neural networks and their applications.
